he opportunity to experience firsthand Howe’s continuation of that elusive and fascinating endeavor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAmerican poetryy20th century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aamerican literature.  aamerican poets.  aart and literature.  acontemporary poetry.  acontradictions.  adoubt.  aemotional.  aenglish majors.  afamous poets.  aheartfelt.  ahuman experiences.  ahumanity.  alit students.  aliterary analysis.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary scholars.  alove and loss.  alove.  alyrical essay.  apoetry collection.  apoetry textbooks.  apoets.  apsyche.  arealism.  arecovery.  ashort poems.  atheology.  aunited states.  aworld relationships.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093710940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937109423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937109/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles